## 6. Uniform Circular Motion

When an object moves in a circular path with constant speed, it is called Uniform Circular Motion.

* **Note:** Even if the speed is constant, the **velocity is changing** because the direction of motion changes at every point. Therefore, circular motion is always an **accelerated motion**.
